Richard asked:

 > Clover brand comes in a nice 2 can attached bottom-to-bottom coarse on one end
and fine on the other. Start with coarse, finish with fine.
 
 And that grit is fine enough for valves? I found this page earlier in my
search that seemed to indicate a finer grit for valve lapping:
 
 http://www.newmantools.com/clover.htm
 
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Yep, works perfect. Anything finer and you end up with a mirror finish. You don't need that.
You just want the valve face to seal to the seat all the way around.
